cron job - automatically scheduled task on a computer
cron jobs are used to run tasks on a schedule (every minutes,hour,day,week and month)
cron job automate repetitive work ,such as 
    backing up files
    cleaning temporary files
    sending emails
    updating database
    running scripts


create the cron jobs    
    crontab -e

add a cron job
    * * * * * command
    | | | | |
    | | | | day of the week (0-6)
    | | | Month(1-12)
    | | day of the month(1-31)
    | Hour
   minutes
   

example:
    */5 * * * * /home/user/myscript.sh          ##it runs the every 5 minutes
    0 10 * * 1 /home/user/myscript.sh           ## It rune every monday 10AM



To check the cron jobs are saved
    crontab -l

To status cron job is running or not 
    systemctl status cron

To see output of the running cron job
    cat <path>

To delete all cron jobs  for your user at once
    crontab -r

To check the cron log 
    grep CRON /var/log/syslog
